WEBVTT

00:00:23.570 --> 00:00:27.580
Hi, I'm Mark Kawano,
Apple's User Experience Evangelist.

00:00:27.630 --> 00:00:29.710
In this video,
I'm going to go through some tips

00:00:29.840 --> 00:00:34.610
to help you with the design and user
experience of your iPhone or iPad app.

00:00:34.680 --> 00:00:38.820
The content I've put together comes from
my experience designing apps at Apple,

00:00:38.890 --> 00:00:42.240
as well as my experience working
with thousands of developers

00:00:42.240 --> 00:00:43.780
from all over the world.

00:00:43.830 --> 00:00:47.420
I will address some of the most
common usability issues in iOS apps,

00:00:47.470 --> 00:00:53.280
and will also show many examples of great
user experiences to educate and inspire.

00:00:53.420 --> 00:00:56.460
Some of the topics may seem familiar to
those of you who have seen some of my

00:00:56.460 --> 00:00:59.420
previous videos on user interface design.

00:00:59.570 --> 00:01:02.280
However,
this is a brand new talk with a lot of

00:01:02.280 --> 00:01:06.660
new tips to help any developer create
a more intuitive and engaging app.

00:01:06.780 --> 00:01:08.460
So let's get started.

00:01:08.510 --> 00:01:11.100
I want to start off by saying
that it would be impossible for me

00:01:11.100 --> 00:01:14.900
to talk about every UI situation
you'll face when designing an app.

00:01:15.030 --> 00:01:16.620
And that's not my intention.

00:01:16.720 --> 00:01:19.560
Like I said earlier,
the content I've put together

00:01:19.560 --> 00:01:23.180
addresses the most common
usability issues in iOS apps.

00:01:25.040 --> 00:01:27.440
To get started,
I want to talk about the importance of

00:01:27.500 --> 00:01:29.150
telling a great story with your app.

00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:31.890
When designing an app,
you should always be thinking about

00:01:31.940 --> 00:01:33.450
the story you're trying to tell.

00:01:33.460 --> 00:01:37.620
Just like the most powerful stories are
able to really captivate an audience,

00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:40.160
well, similarly,
great apps are capable of

00:01:40.200 --> 00:01:43.770
creating an equally powerful
emotional response for its users.

00:01:43.800 --> 00:01:47.960
I know that when I use a great app,
it makes me feel really great,

00:01:48.070 --> 00:01:50.600
and as a developer or a designer,
it's inspiring.

00:01:51.180 --> 00:01:54.140
So when you design your app,
you should constantly think about

00:01:54.140 --> 00:01:55.950
what it takes to tell a great story.

00:01:55.980 --> 00:01:59.870
So to help you tell a great story,
there are a few things to think about.

00:01:59.880 --> 00:02:02.080
First, what will your app do?

00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:04.490
Think of this as the plot for your story.

00:02:04.500 --> 00:02:07.180
It's not enough to just have
an app on the App Store.

00:02:07.200 --> 00:02:09.540
It needs to provide value for its users.

00:02:09.560 --> 00:02:11.630
Next, who are the users?

00:02:11.640 --> 00:02:14.170
When you tell a great story,
it's important to know the

00:02:14.210 --> 00:02:15.840
audience you're telling it to.

00:02:15.840 --> 00:02:18.630
When you design for a
specific user group,

00:02:18.720 --> 00:02:20.940
it will affect every part
of the design process.

00:02:21.160 --> 00:02:23.920
From the feature set,
to the visual design,

00:02:23.920 --> 00:02:25.560
to the interaction metaphors.

00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:29.470
And finally, you also need to think
about the story's settings.

00:02:29.520 --> 00:02:32.590
The iPhone and the iPad
are mobile devices,

00:02:32.590 --> 00:02:36.300
and they're not used in the same settings
as traditional software or websites.

00:02:36.400 --> 00:02:39.690
I know that I use my iPhone
or iPad throughout the day,

00:02:39.690 --> 00:02:40.720
wherever I am.

00:02:40.800 --> 00:02:44.030
Designing a great product
doesn't start or end with a list

00:02:44.030 --> 00:02:45.970
of features or technologies.

00:02:45.980 --> 00:02:48.860
At the end of the day,
people care about how your app makes

00:02:48.900 --> 00:02:51.140
them feel and what it enables them to do.

00:02:51.160 --> 00:02:52.670
to do.

00:02:52.790 --> 00:02:57.020
And this is why in our ads,
we don't talk about RAM, processor speed,

00:02:57.130 --> 00:02:58.410
or all the other technologies.

00:02:58.420 --> 00:03:02.920
Instead, we focus on all the great things
that you can do with our products.

00:03:02.920 --> 00:03:06.230
The features and technologies
that you include in your app

00:03:06.620 --> 00:03:09.330
should only be there to support
the story you're trying to tell.

00:03:09.390 --> 00:03:13.920
And I find it really helpful to envision
a 30-second commercial of your product

00:03:13.920 --> 00:03:16.340
at the beginning of the design process.

00:03:16.680 --> 00:03:19.890
And this will really help you focus
on the most important screens,

00:03:19.890 --> 00:03:23.280
the most important features,
and the overall visual design that you're

00:03:23.280 --> 00:03:25.110
going to be using throughout your app.

00:03:27.780 --> 00:03:30.700
So throughout your design process,
always think about how

00:03:30.700 --> 00:03:32.380
to tell a great story.

00:03:32.420 --> 00:03:34.620
And above all else,
your goal should be to

00:03:34.620 --> 00:03:38.040
create an experience that
enables and delights people.

00:03:38.140 --> 00:03:40.420
And if you're able to
accomplish this goal,

00:03:40.470 --> 00:03:43.410
I can guarantee it's one of
the most rewarding feelings

00:03:43.410 --> 00:03:45.100
you'll get as a developer.

